go_repository: drop a fetched Go module's own MODULE.bazel before generation.

Gazelle's go language reads the repo-local MODULE.bazel to resolve the
apparent name of rules_go (language/go/config.go: ExtractModuleToApparentName
Mapping). For repos generated by the go_deps module extension this is wrong:
the fetched module's bazel_deps are not part of our module graph, so gazelle
emits load("@rules_go//...") while the extension-provided repo mapping only
supplies the legacy "io_bazel_rules_go" name, breaking every generated BUILD
file in that repo (observed with github.com/lestrrat-go/jwx/v3, which ships a
full Bazel workspace). A go_deps repo is a plain Go module by definition;
delete the file so generation falls back to the mapped legacy name.

--- a/internal/go_repository.bzl
+++ b/internal/go_repository.bzl
@@ -299,6 +299,12 @@

     if generate:
         # Build file generation is needed. Populate Gazelle directive at root build file
+        # A go_deps-generated repo is a plain Go module: its own MODULE.bazel
+        # (if shipped) declares bazel_deps outside our module graph, and
+        # letting Gazelle read it makes generated files reference apparent
+        # repo names the extension's repo mapping does not provide.
+        if is_module_extension_repo and ctx.path("MODULE.bazel").exists:
+            ctx.delete("MODULE.bazel")
         build_file_name = existing_build_file or build_file_names[0]
         if len(ctx.attr.build_directives) > 0:
             ctx.file(
